					<div id="mw-content-text" class="mw-body-content"><div class="mw-content-ltr mw-parser-output" lang="en" dir="ltr"><div class="shortdescription nomobile noexcerpt noprint searchaux" style="display:none">Oldest scriptures of Hinduism</div>
<p class="mw-empty-elt">
</p>
<style data-mw-deduplicate="TemplateStyles:r1033289096">.mw-parser-output .hatnote{font-style:italic}.mw-parser-output div.hatnote{padding-left:1.6em;margin-bottom:0.5em}.mw-parser-output .hatnote i{font-style:normal}.mw-parser-output .hatnote+link+.hatnote{margin-top:-0.5em}</style><div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable">"Veda" and "Vedic" redirect here. For other uses, see <a href="/wiki/Veda_(disambiguation)" class="mw-disambig" title="Veda (disambiguation)">Veda (disambiguation)</a> and <a href="/wiki/Vedic_(disambiguation)" class="mw-disambig" title="Vedic (disambiguation)">Vedic (disambiguation)</a>.</div>
<p class="mw-empty-elt">

</p>
