<li id="cite_note-258"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-258">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Elisa Freschi (2012): "The Vedas are not <a href="/wiki/Deontological_ethics" class="mw-redirect" title="Deontological ethics">deontic</a> authorities in absolute sense and may be disobeyed, but are recognized as a deontological <a href="/wiki/Epistemology" title="Epistemology">epistemic</a> authority by a Hindu orthodox school."<sup id="cite_ref-FOOTNOTEFreschi201262_257-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-FOOTNOTEFreschi201262-257">&#91;235&#93;</a></sup> This differentiation between epistemic and deontic authority is true for all Indian religions.</span>
